12 SECTION 3. IC 26-3-8-16, AS AMENDED BY P.L.144-2014,
13 SECTION 8, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
14 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 16. (a) This chapter does not impair the power of
15 the parties to a rental agreement to create rights, duties, or obligations
16 that do not arise from this chapter. The rights provided to an owner by
17 this chapter are in addition to all other rights provided by law to a
18 creditor against a debtor.
19 (b) A rental agreement may specify a limit on the value of personal
20 property that may be stored in a renter's rented space. If a rental
21 agreement specifies a limit on the value of stored personal property
22 under this subsection, the limit specified in the rental agreement is
23 considered the maximum value of the renter's personal property stored
24 in the renter's rented space.
25 (c) If a person does not sign a rental agreement delivered by the
26 owner to the person:
27 (1) in person;
28 (2) by electronic mail; or
29 (3) by first class mail that is addressed to the last known
30 address of the person;
31 the person's continued use of a storage space at the self-service
32 storage facility for thirty (30) or more days from the date that the
33 owner delivered the rental agreement to the person shall constitute
34 an acceptance of the rental agreement as though it had been signed
35 by the person.
36 (d) Subject to subsection (i), an owner may terminate or choose
37 not to renew a rental agreement between the owner and a renter if
38 the owner:
39 (1) delivers a written notice to the renter:
40 (A) in person;
41 (B) by electronic mail; or
42 (C) by verified mail that is addressed to the last known
