16 any storage space located at the self-service storage facility,
17 including denying the former renter access to the self-service
18 storage facility and any storage space located at the self-service
19 storage facility for any purpose other than the former renter's
20 removal of all of the former renter's personal property from the
21 self-service storage facility.
22 (g) An owner may dispose of any personal property belonging
23 to a former renter that remains:
24 (1) in a storage space at the self-service storage facility; or
25 (2) on the premises of the self-service storage facility;
26 for more than thirty (30) days after the termination or nonrenewal
27 of a rental agreement between the owner and a former renter.
28 (h) A rental agreement may contain a provision notifying the
29 renter of the owner's right to dispose of personal property that
30 remains:
31 (1) in a storage space at the self-service storage facility; or
32 (2) on the premises of the self-service storage facility;
33 for more than thirty (30) days after the termination or nonrenewal
34 of a rental agreement.
35 (i) An owner may not deliver a notice under subsection (d) or
36 take action under subsection (f) or (g) if the renter is subject to lien
37 enforcement under section 12 of this chapter.
38 (j) A rental agreement may be delivered and executed
39 electronically.
