COMMITTEE REPORT
Mr. President: The Senate Committee on Judiciary, to which was
referred Senate Bill No. 118, has had the same under consideration and
begs leave to report the same back to the Senate with the
recommendation that said bill be AMENDED as follows:
Page 3, line 36, delete "An" and insert "Subject to subsection (i),
an".
Page 4, line 25, delete "fifteen (15)" and insert "thirty (30)".
Page 4, line 32, delete "fifteen (15)" and insert "thirty (30)".
Page 4, between lines 33 and 34, begin a new paragraph and insert:
"(i) An owner may not deliver a notice under subsection (d) or
take action under subsection (f) or (g) if the renter is subject to lien
enforcement under section 12 of this chapter.".
Page 4, line 34, delete "(i)" and insert "(j)".
and when so amended that said bill do pass.
(Reference is to SB 118 as introduced.)
